---
id: org.dxos.plugin.feed
name: FeedPlugin
version: 0.2.0
---

A Composer plugin for syndicated content. Today it supports RSS and ATproto
Feeds whose Posts are synced into the space as ECHO objects. This revision
adds **Magazines** — agent-curated collections of articles drawn from one or
more Feeds and displayed as a Masonry grid. The user describes in natural
language what content a Magazine should gather; pressing *Curate* triggers
feed sync followed by an agent that selects matching articles, fetches their
text and hero images, and appends them to the Magazine.

The design also scaffolds (schema-only) a future tagging feature in which the
agent assigns tags to curated Posts to enable navigation, filtering, and
feed-discovery flows.

## Extensions

The following extension dialects are used in this document.

| Term        | URI                            |
|-------------|--------------------------------|
| `type`      | `org.dxos.mdl.type@1.0`        |
| `feat`      | `org.dxos.mdl.feat@1.0`        |
| `test`      | `org.dxos.mdl.test@1.0`        |
| `component` | `org.dxos.mdl.component@1.0`   |
| `op`        | `org.dxos.mdl.op@1.0`          |
| `service`   | `org.dxos.mdl.service@1.0`     |

## Types

```mdl
type FeedType
  literals: atproto | rss
```

```mdl
type Feed
  desc: >
    A subscription source. Existing type — documented here for context.
    SyncFeed pulls Posts from the URL into the space.
  fields:
    name?: string
    url?: string
    type?: FeedType
    description?: string
    link?: string
    iconUrl?: string
    cursor?: string                 # sync state
    feed?: Ref<Queue>               # backing ECHO feed
```

```mdl
type Post
  desc: >
    An individual syndicated article. Existing fields are unchanged.
    This revision adds four optional fields populated by the Magazine
    curation flow. All additions are optional — existing Posts remain valid.
  fields:
    title?: string
    link?: string                   # URL of the original article
    description?: string            # feed-provided summary (as-is)
    author?: string
    published?: string              # ISO 8601 publication date
    guid?: string                   # feed-provided unique id

    # --- Additions ---
    snippet?: string                # agent-extracted short text (~200 chars)
    imageUrl?: string               # hero image URL extracted from the article page
    readAt?: string                 # ISO 8601; presence = read, absence = unread
    tags?: string[]                 # agent-assigned tags (future tagging feature; always [] today)
```

```mdl
type Magazine
  desc: >
    An agent-curated collection of articles drawn from one or more Feeds.
    The user describes what content the Magazine should gather via a
    long-form instructions Text. The agent reads the instructions, selects
    matching Posts from the referenced Feeds, enriches them with snippet
    and hero image, and appends their refs to `posts`.
  fields:
    name?: string
    feeds: Ref<Feed>[]              # Feeds to pull from
    instructions: Ref<Text>         # long-form curation brief (not rendered as form input)
    posts: Ref<Post>[]              # curated Post refs (insertion order; UI displays newest-last reversed)
  annotations:
    icon: ph--newspaper-clipping--regular
    hue: indigo
    label: name
```

## Components

```mdl
component MagazineArticle
  desc: >
    Article surface bound to a Magazine object. Shows curated articles in a
    Masonry grid and offers a Curate button that triggers feed sync plus
    agent curation.
  props:
    magazine: Magazine
  state:
    running: boolean                # Curate flow in progress
    phase?: 'syncing' | 'curating'  # shown as button tooltip while running
    readerPost?: Post               # open article in the inline reader when set
  slots:
    header?: ReactNode
  actions:
    curate()                        # run syncFeeds → invoke MagazineBlueprint agent
    openReader(post: Post)          # show ArticleReader; sets post.readAt if unset
    closeReader()
  emits:
    onCurateComplete(added: number)
  layout: |
    ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────┐
    │ [header slot]                 [✨ Curate]   │
    ├─────────────────────────────────────────────┤
    │ ┌─────┐ ┌─────┐ ┌─────┐                     │
    │ │tile │ │tile │ │tile │   (Masonry grid)    │
    │ └─────┘ └─────┘ └─────┘                     │
    │ ┌─────┐ ┌─────┐                             │
    │ │tile │ │tile │                             │
    │ └─────┘ └─────┘                             │
    └─────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

```mdl
component MagazineTile
  desc: >
    Single masonry cell rendering a curated Post. Dimmed when post.readAt is set.
    Click opens the ArticleReader. Tags row appears only when tags.length > 0.
  props:
    post: Post
    feed: Feed                      # resolved parent feed for name/icon
  emits:
    onOpen(post: Post)
  layout: |
    ┌─────────────────────────┐
    │ [hero image if present] │
    ├─────────────────────────┤
    │ Title (2-line clamp)    │
    │ Snippet (3-line clamp)  │
    │ ─────────────────────── │
    │ Feed · Author · Date    │
    │ [#tag] [#tag]           │   (only when tags.length > 0)
    └─────────────────────────┘
```

```mdl
component ArticleReader
  desc: >
    Inline overlay (dialog/sheet) inside the MagazineArticle surface.
    Displays the extracted snippet and a link-out to the original article.
    Sets post.readAt on open if not already set.
  props:
    post: Post
    feed: Feed
  emits:
    onClose()
  layout: |
    ┌───────────────────────────────────────┐
    │ [hero image]                     [✕]  │
    ├───────────────────────────────────────┤
    │ Title                                 │
    │ Feed · Author · Date                  │
    ├───────────────────────────────────────┤
    │ Snippet (full)                        │
    │                                       │
    ├───────────────────────────────────────┤
    │              [Open original ↗]        │
    └───────────────────────────────────────┘
```

## Services

```mdl
service MagazineBlueprint
  desc: |
    Agent blueprint invoked by the MagazineArticle Curate button.
    Registered as a BlueprintDefinition capability. The agent reads the
    Magazine's instructions Text and referenced feeds, selects matching
    Posts, and enriches them.
  key: org.dxos.blueprint.magazine
  ops:
    # All operations are exposed as tools:
    # - ListCandidatePosts
    # - FetchArticleContent
    # - AddPostToMagazine
  note: >
    Uses Template.make() for its prompt. The prompt instructs the agent to
    call ListCandidatePosts, then for each selected Post call
    FetchArticleContent and AddPostToMagazine. Dedup is enforced by the tools,
    not the prompt.
```

## Operations

```mdl
op SyncFeed
  desc: Existing operation. Pulls new Posts from a Feed's source URL.
  input:
    feedId: DXN
  output: number                   # number of Posts added
  effects: [http, echo:write]
  note: Documented here for context; unchanged by this revision.
```

```mdl
op ListCandidatePosts
  desc: >
    Returns lightweight summaries of Posts from the Magazine's referenced
    feeds that have NOT yet been added to the Magazine. Excludes Posts whose
    refs already appear in magazine.posts.
  input:
    magazineId: DXN
  output:
    Array<{
      postId: DXN,
      feedName?: string,
      title?: string,
      description?: string,
      author?: string,
      published?: string
    }>
  effects: [echo:read]
  note: >
    Deliberately excludes the full article body and image — the agent
    decides from summaries whether to call FetchArticleContent.
```

```mdl
op FetchArticleContent
  desc: >
    Fetches post.link over HTTP and returns extracted plain text plus any
    image URLs found (og:image and <img> tags). Pure read — does not mutate
    the Post. Reusable by the future tagging feature.
  input:
    postId: DXN
  output:
    {
      text: string,
      imageUrls: string[]
    }
  errors:
    FetchFailed: HTTP error or network failure
    NoLink: the Post has no `link` field
  effects: [http, echo:read]
```

```mdl
op AddPostToMagazine
  desc: >
    Writes snippet and imageUrl onto the Post and appends the Post's ref to
    magazine.posts. Idempotent — no-op if the Post ref is already present.
  input:
    magazineId: DXN
    postId: DXN
    snippet: string
    imageUrl?: string
  output: Post
  effects: [echo:write]
```

```mdl
op CurateMagazine
  desc: >
    Deterministic one-shot curation invoked by the Curate button. For each
    uncurated candidate Post, derives a snippet and hero image from the Post's
    existing `description` (no HTTP) and appends the enriched Post ref to
    `magazine.posts`. Skips Posts with empty descriptions.
  input:
    magazineId: DXN
  output:
    added: number
  effects: [echo:write]
  note: >
    Exists alongside the blueprint. The deterministic path gives the button
    an immediate, reliable result without needing an LLM. The agent path
    (via the blueprint's fine-grained tools) delivers instruction-driven,
    higher-quality curation through chat.
```

## Features

```mdl
feat F-1: Magazine Type
  desc: Introduce the Magazine ECHO type with feeds, instructions, and curated posts.

  req F-1.1: User can create a Magazine object via the plugin's create menu.
  req F-1.2: Magazine.name is optional; magazine is labeled by name when set.
  req F-1.3: Magazine.feeds is an array of Ref<Feed>; empty by default.
  req F-1.4: Magazine.instructions is a Ref<Text>; hidden from the standard form input.
  req F-1.5: Magazine.posts is an array of Ref<Post>; empty by default; insertion order preserved.
```

```mdl
feat F-2: Post Extensions
  desc: Add optional snippet, imageUrl, readAt, and tags to existing Post type.

  req F-2.1: All new fields are optional; existing Post objects load unchanged.
  req F-2.2: snippet is a plain string; no max length enforced at schema level.
  req F-2.3: imageUrl is a plain string URL.
  req F-2.4: readAt is an ISO 8601 timestamp; presence = read, absence = unread.
  req F-2.5: tags is a string array; defaults to empty; not populated in this revision.
```

```mdl
feat F-3: Magazine Curate Flow
  desc: Sync referenced feeds then invoke the agent to curate articles.

  req F-3.1: MagazineArticle toolbar includes a Curate button.
  req F-3.2:
    when: user clicks Curate
    then: button shows spinner, is disabled, tooltip shows phase ('Syncing feeds...' / 'Curating articles...')
  req F-3.3:
    when: Curate runs
    then: SyncFeed invoked in parallel for each Ref in magazine.feeds; per-feed failures are collected but do not abort the flow
  req F-3.4:
    when: all feed syncs resolve (success or failure)
    then: CurateMagazine operation is invoked with the Magazine ref
  req F-3.5:
    when: CurateMagazine completes
    then: button returns to idle; reactive UI renders the new tiles
  req F-3.6:
    when: magazine.feeds is empty
    then: Curate button is disabled with tooltip 'Add at least one feed first'
  req F-3.7: Re-clicking Curate while running is a no-op (button disabled; in-memory running flag).
```

```mdl
feat F-4: Agent Curation Behavior
  desc: Agent uses tools to select, fetch, and add Posts.

  req F-4.1: Agent reads magazine.instructions Text and magazine.feeds refs from context.
  req F-4.2: Agent calls ListCandidatePosts(magazineId) to receive unenriched candidates.
  req F-4.3: Agent filters candidates against the instructions and skips low-relevance posts.
  req F-4.4: For each selected Post, agent calls FetchArticleContent(postId) to obtain text and images.
  req F-4.5: Agent produces a concise snippet (target ~200 chars) and selects the best image URL.
  req F-4.6: Agent calls AddPostToMagazine(magazineId, postId, snippet, imageUrl).
  req F-4.7: AddPostToMagazine is idempotent; re-invocation with the same postId is a no-op append.
```

```mdl
feat F-5: Masonry Display
  desc: Render curated Posts in a Masonry grid with rich tiles.

  req F-5.1: MagazineArticle renders magazine.posts in reverse insertion order (newest first) in a Masonry grid.
  req F-5.2: Each tile shows imageUrl (if present), title, snippet, feed name, author, published date.
  req F-5.3: Tile tags row renders only when post.tags.length > 0.
  req F-5.4: Tiles where post.readAt is set are visually dimmed.
  req F-5.5: Clicking a tile opens the ArticleReader for that Post.
  req F-5.6: Opening the reader sets post.readAt to the current ISO timestamp if not already set.
  req F-5.7: Empty state — when magazine.posts is empty — shows: 'No articles yet. Add feeds and press Curate.'
  req F-5.8: Grid uses the @dxos/react-ui-masonry Masonry component.
```

```mdl
feat F-6: Inline Article Reader
  desc: Lightweight reader for curated snippets.

  req F-6.1: ArticleReader is rendered as an overlay inside MagazineArticle; no route change.
  req F-6.2: Reader shows hero image, title, feed name, author, date, full snippet.
  req F-6.3: Reader includes an 'Open original' button linking to post.link (new tab/window).
  req F-6.4: Closing the reader restores focus to the tile that opened it.
```

```mdl
feat F-7: Future Tagging (schema scaffolding only)
  desc: Schema fields in place so the tagging feature composes without migration.

  req F-7.1: Post.tags exists as Schema.Array(Schema.String).pipe(Schema.optional).
  req F-7.2: MagazineTile renders a tags row conditionally on tags.length > 0.
  req F-7.3: FetchArticleContent is reusable as the input stage for a future TagPosts operation.
  note: >
    Later features (out of scope): TagPosts operation, a MagazineTagger blueprint
    (or extension of MagazineBlueprint), tag-filter chips in the toolbar,
    'Find more like this' action, and 'Suggest feeds' action proposing new Feed
    URLs based on accumulated tag distribution.
```

## Acceptance

```mdl
test T-1: Create Magazine
  given: user is in a space in Composer
  when: user creates a Magazine via the plugin's create menu
  then:
    - Magazine object created in space
    - Magazine.feeds is an empty array
    - Magazine.posts is an empty array
    - Magazine.instructions is a Ref to an empty Text object
```

```mdl
test T-2: Post schema backward compatibility
  given: a Post created before this revision exists in the space
  when: the new plugin version loads
  then:
    - Post loads without schema error
    - Post.snippet, Post.imageUrl, Post.readAt, Post.tags are all undefined / empty
```

```mdl
test T-3: Curate button disabled without feeds
  given: a Magazine with magazine.feeds.length === 0
  when: MagazineArticle renders
  then:
    - Curate button is disabled
    - tooltip text === 'Add at least one feed first'
```

```mdl
test T-4: Curate flow runs sync then deterministic curation
  given: a Magazine with two referenced feeds, each with unsynced remote posts
  when: user clicks Curate
  then:
    - SyncFeed invoked once per referenced feed
    - After all SyncFeed calls resolve, CurateMagazine operation is invoked
    - Magazine.posts grows by the count returned from CurateMagazine
    - Button returns to idle
```

```mdl
test T-4a: Agent curation via blueprint
  given: a chat referencing a Magazine whose MagazineBlueprint is active
  when: the agent is prompted to curate the magazine
  then:
    - Agent calls ListCandidatePosts, FetchArticleContent, AddPostToMagazine
    - Magazine.posts grows by the agent-selected count
  note: >
    The blueprint path is distinct from the Curate button (T-4). The button
    runs the deterministic CurateMagazine op; agents invoke the fine-grained
    tools through chat.
```

```mdl
test T-5: Partial feed sync failure is non-fatal
  given: a Magazine with two feeds; one feed's URL returns 500
  when: user clicks Curate
  then:
    - CurateMagazine still runs against posts from the successful feed
    - Error surfaced via a localized message in the status bar
```

```mdl
test T-6: ListCandidatePosts excludes curated
  given: a Magazine whose posts array already contains refs to two Posts from feed A
  when: ListCandidatePosts(magazineId) is called
  then: returned list contains no entries whose postId matches an existing magazine.posts ref
```

```mdl
test T-7: AddPostToMagazine is idempotent
  given: a Magazine already containing a Post ref
  when: AddPostToMagazine invoked with the same postId
  then:
    - magazine.posts length unchanged
    - Post.snippet and Post.imageUrl left unchanged (no overwrite on duplicate)
```

```mdl
test T-8: FetchArticleContent surfaces images
  given: a Post whose link resolves to an HTML page with og:image and two <img> tags
  when: FetchArticleContent(postId) is called
  then:
    - output.text contains the page's main text
    - output.imageUrls includes the og:image URL
    - output.imageUrls includes URLs from <img> tags
```

```mdl
test T-9: Tile dimming on read
  given: a Magazine with one Post where readAt is unset
  when: user clicks the tile
  then:
    - ArticleReader opens for that Post
    - Post.readAt is set to an ISO timestamp
    - On reader close, the tile renders dimmed
```

```mdl
test T-10: Tile metadata
  given: a curated Post with title, snippet, imageUrl, author, published, and a feed with name
  when: MagazineTile renders
  then:
    - hero image rendered from imageUrl
    - title rendered with 2-line clamp
    - snippet rendered with 3-line clamp
    - metadata row shows feed name, author, and a formatted date
    - tags row is NOT rendered (tags is empty)
```

---

## Design Notes

### Content Flow

Two curation paths exist side-by-side:

- **Button path (deterministic).** The Curate toolbar button runs `SyncFeed`
  per referenced feed, then invokes `CurateMagazine`. Snippets and images are
  derived from each Post's existing `description` field (no HTTP, no LLM).
  Chosen for the user-initiated button because it is fast, reliable, and does
  not depend on an LLM runtime being present.
- **Agent path (blueprint).** The `MagazineBlueprint` exposes three fine-grained
  tools (`ListCandidatePosts`, `FetchArticleContent`, `AddPostToMagazine`) and
  an instruction template that tells an agent to consult `Magazine.instructions`
  when selecting Posts. Triggered when an agent chat references the Magazine —
  not when the button is clicked. Delivers higher-quality curation (full-article
  fetch + LLM-driven selection) at the cost of latency and LLM availability.

`SyncFeed` is always run deterministically (either by the button or outside
the scope of this feature). Neither curation path fetches feed indices on its
own — that is `SyncFeed`'s job.

### Tool Granularity

Three tools rather than one combined `curateMagazine` tool:

- `ListCandidatePosts` returns lightweight summaries so the agent can triage
  cheaply without loading article bodies.
- `FetchArticleContent` is a read-only HTTP fetch + extract; it is reusable by
  the future `TagPosts` operation which will need the same inputs.
- `AddPostToMagazine` is the sole mutation. Idempotence lives in this tool
  (by ref-set membership check) rather than in the prompt.

Quality of selection is the agent's job; the tools deliberately don't try to
rank or filter on the agent's behalf.

### Snippet Storage

`Post.snippet` is a plain inline string, not a `Ref<Text>`. Snippets are
short (~200 chars target) and read-only to the user; the `Ref<Text>` indirection
used for `Agent.instructions` and `Magazine.instructions` is appropriate for
long-form, user-editable content and is not needed here.

### Read State

Represented as an optional ISO timestamp `readAt`, not a boolean or enum.
Absence = unread; presence = read (at that time). This leaves room to show
"read 2 days ago" or to expire reads without a schema change.

### Image Extraction

`FetchArticleContent` returns a list of candidate image URLs; the agent picks
the "best" one for the Post's `imageUrl`. The prompt should prefer `og:image`
when present. If no suitable image exists the Post is still added with
`imageUrl` undefined — `MagazineTile` renders without the image region.

HTML parsing uses whatever parser the existing codebase already uses for
similar tasks. If no parser is in use, `linkedom` is the proposed addition —
small, no-DOM-globals footprint, works in Node and browser. Addition of a
parser dependency is a decision point flagged during implementation planning.

### Deduplication Policy

Deduplication is keyed on Post ref identity, not on URL or guid. If a Post is
removed from the Magazine and later re-curated, the agent will re-add it.
Dedup across a Feed's historical sync is out of scope — `Feed` already
deduplicates on `guid` when syncing.

### Relationship to Future Tagging

The tagging feature is strictly additive to this design:

- `Post.tags` already exists as an optional string array.
- `FetchArticleContent` is the reusable read-stage for tagging.
- `MagazineTile` renders a tags row when non-empty — no UI change needed.
- A `TagPosts` operation and either an extended prompt in `MagazineBlueprint`
  or a second `MagazineTagger` blueprint will complete the feature in a later
  revision.

Further future work enabled by tags (all out of scope here): tag-filter chips
in the Magazine toolbar; a "Find more like this" action prompting the agent
to curate Posts with overlapping tags; a "Suggest feeds" action proposing new
Feed URLs based on accumulated tag distribution.

### Out of Scope

- Rendering the full original article body inside the reader (would require
  storing full extracted text; current design stores only the snippet).
- Scheduled / background Curate runs — this revision only supports the
  explicit toolbar-triggered flow.
- Cross-Magazine deduplication — two Magazines may both curate the same Post.
- Editing or regenerating a snippet after curation — re-curation is the path
  to different content.
